Yet Another way to use Windows VST plugins on Linux. Yabridge seamlessly
supports using both 32-bit and 64-bit Windows VST2 and VST3 plugins in a
64-bit Linux VST host as if they were native VST2 and VST3 plugins, with
optional support for plugin groups to enable inter-plugin communication
for VST2 plugins and quick startup times. Its modern concurrent
architecture and focus on transparency allows yabridge to be both fast
and highly compatible, while also staying easy to debug and maintain.

This script will build yabridge with both 64bit and 32bit plugin support
and yabridgectl helper tool on Slackware64. This script depends on any
wine version and multilib, but wine-tkg is recommended.
The script depends on a internet connection for meson subprojects.

Make sure you have configured you're system with real-time priority.
Read the documentation in /usr/doc/yabridge-4.0.0/
These are Markdown files from github,
I will convert them to sample text and html soon
and include them here, to make life easy for the user
In the meantime you could read from:

https://github.com/robbert-vdh/yabridge/tree/b826f800374d0b6392ac17847fb599e47ec2accc

OPTIONAL DEPENDENCE: winetricks
